                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/phys-514" class="program-course-title">
              PHYS 514 General Relativity (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-33619" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Physics (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Physics              : Transition from special to general relativity. Non-Euclidian geometry. The basic laws of Physics in co-variant form, Einstein's equations. Gravitational waves; neutron stars; black holes; cosmology.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Robert Brandenberger (Winter)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Winter</li>
              <li>3 hours lectures</li>
              <li>Restriction: U3 Honours students and graduate students, or permission of the instructor.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/phys-519" class="program-course-title">
              PHYS 519 Advanced Biophysics (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-33621" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
