                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/phys-567" class="program-course-title">
              PHYS 567 Particle Physics (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-33637" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Physics (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Physics              : Survey of elementary particles; hadrons, leptons and hadrons' constituents (quarks). Invariance principles and conservation laws. Detectors and accelerators. Phenomenology of strong, electromagnetic and weak interactions.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        James M Cline (Winter)                  </p>

    
